pdgm.pdgmnote: Huehnergard2005 p. 11,272;akkadian_OB uses three different sets of independent pronouns depending on the case of the pronoun.
Huehnergard2005 p. 273-74;appear as predicates of a verbless clause (\the house is mine\) or to emphasize possession. See Huehnergard p. 273 for more information.
HUEHNEGARD2005 pp. 84-89;1cs possessive suffix varies:-ī before \all singular nouns and adjectives in the nom. and acc.\;otherwise,-ya is used.

Huehnergard p. 169;Akkadian/OB attaches two sets of suffixes on verbal forms,one paradigm for the acc. and another for the dat. Huehnergard puts both sets under the heading \Object Pronominal Suffixes on the Verb,\§18.2.
